In this article, President Biden speaks about his recent trip to New Jersey and New York to provide help to those affected by recent events. He expresses confidence in their ability to change the circumstances and mentions that the trip went well. When asked about his plans to combat the COVID-19 pandemic, the President mentions that he will talk about it in more detail the following day. He is then asked about the possibility of defeating the pandemic or just controlling it, to which he defers the answer to his upcoming speech. The President is also asked about concerns regarding China funding the Taliban, to which he states that China, along with other countries like Pakistan, Russia, and Iran, are trying to figure out their approach to the Taliban. The President briefly mentions his communication with Senator Manchin and expresses optimism in reaching an agreement. When asked about the timing of the reconciliation bill, he states that he is comfortable with the current proceedings.